title: 'The stench of death hangs in the air': On the ground at aftermath of India train crash
description: The room is vast, cold and the stench of death hangs in the air.

title: Governor of border region 'willing to meet' group who captured two Russian soldiers
description: A Russian governor has said he is willing to meet with a pro-Ukraine group of Russian fighters who are keeping two Russian soldiers captive.

title: Suspect in unsolved student disappearance set to be 'extradited to US on Tuesday'
description: The main suspect in the unsolved disappearance of American student Natalee Holloway in 2005 has been transferred to a prison near Peru's capital ahead of his pending extradition to the United States.

title: Real Madrid legend Karim Benzema to leave after 14 years
description: Real Madrid's talismanic captain Karim Benzema will leave the Bernabeu after 14 years, the Spanish club has confirmed.

title: Belgian prime minister knocked out after falling off bike
description: Belgian Prime Minister Alexander De Croo fell off his bike and briefly lost consciousness while out for a ride with his son.

title: Signal failure likely caused train to change tracks before crash, says minister
description: India's deadly rail crash was likely caused by a signalling failure that caused a train to wrongly change tracks, the country's railway minister has said.

title: Oil tanker breaks down and disrupts traffic in Suez Canal
description: An oil tanker broke down in the Suez Canal on Sunday, disrupting traffic in the vital global waterway.

title: Zelenskyy and Klitschko clash after woman killed outside locked air raid shelter
description: A woman is believed to have been killed in Kyiv while waiting outside a locked air raid shelter - as inspections revealed nearly a quarter of Ukraine's shelters were locked or unusable.

title: Eight arrested in Hong Kong on anniversary of Tiananmen Square massacre
description: Eight people have been arrested in Hong Kong as part of a crackdown on protests on the anniversary of the Tiananmen Square massacre.

title: 'The carriages crushed us': Hospital resembles war zone in town on front line of India's rail tragedy
description: At Balasore General Hospital, room after room is full of the injured - many on the floor and in corridors.

title: Football game suspended after fan dies in 15-metre fall from stadium
description: A football game in Argentina had to be suspended after a supporter fell from the stadium.
